7 .
a group of tasks that can be executed in parallel without requiring data shuffle
A stage in Spark is a set of parallel tasks that can be executed without shuffle. Stages are created based on shuffle boundaries,
where wide transformations like joins or groupBy trigger a new stage.

8.
a unit of execution triggered when an action is called on a DataFrame or RDD
A job in Spark is triggered by an action and represents the execution of a DAG. It is divided into stages based on shuffle boundaries,
and each stage is further divided into tasks executed in parallel.


9. A task is the smallest unit of execution in Spark, where each task processes one partition of data and runs on an executor core in parallel.”
